On January 28, 2009, the board of directors (the "") of AutoNation, Inc. (the "") authorized and approved letter agreements with certain automotive manufacturers in order to, among other things, eliminate any potential adverse consequences under such manufacturers' framework agreements with the Company in the event that ESL Investments, Inc. and certain investment affiliates of ESL Investments, Inc. (together, "") acquires fifty percent (50%) or more of the Company's Common Stock (the ""). The letter agreements with American Honda Motor Co., Inc. ("") and Toyota Motor Sales, U.S.A., Inc ("") (such agreements, the "" and the "," respectively), which were entered into on January 28, 2009, also contain governance-related and other provisions as described below. Also a party to both the Honda and Toyota Agreements is ESL, the Company's largest shareholder. ESL currently owns approximately forty-five percent (45%) of the Common Stock.
