4.4 . If the obligation of any Lender to make a Eurodollar Rate Loan or a Competitive Bid Loan bearing interest at a Eurodollar Competitive Rate or to Continue, or to Convert Loans of any other Type into, Loans of a particular Type shall be suspended pursuant to or hereof (Loans of such Type being herein called "Affected Loans" and such Type being herein called the "Affected Type"), such Lender's Affected Loans shall be automatically Converted into Base Rate Loans on the last day(s) of the then current Interest Period(s) for Affected Loans (or, in the case of a Conversion required by hereof, on such earlier date as such Lender may specify to the Borrower with a copy to the Administrative Agent) and, unless and until such Lender gives notice as provided below that the circumstances specified in or hereof that gave rise to such Conversion no longer exist:
Treatment of Affected Loans
