(i) any other circumstance whatsoever (with or without notice to or knowledge of any Guarantor) which may or might in any manner or to any extent vary the risks of such Guarantor, or might otherwise constitute a legal or equitable defense available to, or discharge of, a surety or a guarantor, including without limitation any right to require or claim that resort be had to the Borrower or any other Guarantor or to any collateral in respect of the Borrower's Liabilities or Guarantors' Obligations (other than (subject to hereof) payment in full of the Borrower's Liabilities and occurrence of the Facility Termination Date.)
